====保加尔人====

[[File:53-manasses-chronicle.jpg|thumb]][[汗_(頭銜)|汗]]追击[[拜占庭帝国|东罗马]]]]

{{Main article|保加尔人|旧大保加利亚}}

[[File:Bulgarians_and_Slavs_VI-VII_century.png|thumb]]的迁徙]]

保加尔人是7世纪兴起于[[东欧大草原|东欧大草原]]和伏尔加河流域的半游牧[[突厥語民族|突厥]]军事部落，发源于[[阿的里-烏拉爾|阿的里-烏拉爾]]地区的骑马游牧民，一些研究者认为其根源可追溯至[[中亚|中亚]]<ref name="Kim">{{cite book |author=Hyun Jin Kim |year=2013 |title=The Huns, Rome and the Birth of Europe |url=https://books.google.hr/books?id=jCpncXFzoFgC |publisher=Cambridge University Press |pages=58–59, 150–155, 168, 204, 243 |isbn=9781107009066 |access-date=2020-07-12 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304082736/https://books.google.hr/books?id=jCpncXFzoFgC |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在他们沿着[[欧亚大草原|欧亚大草原]]一路向西的迁徙中，保加尔人吸收了其他族群和文化影响，其中包括[[匈人|匈人]]和印欧民族{{sfn|Golden|1992|p=253, 256|ps=: "[Pontic Bulgars] With their Avar and Türk political heritage, they assumed political leadership over an array of Turkic groups, Iranians and Finno-Ugric peoples, under the overlordship of the Khazars, whose vassals they remained." ... "The Bulgars, whose Oguric ancestors ..."}}<ref>{{cite book |first=Rosamond |last=McKitterick |author-link= |date=1995 |title=The New Cambridge Medieval History |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZEaSdNBL0sgC |publisher=Cambridge University Press |page=229 |isbn=9780521362924 |quote=The exact ethnic origins of the Danubian Bulgars is controversial. It is in any case most probable that they had enveloped groupings of diverse origins during their migration westwards across the Eurasian steppes, and they undoubtedly spoke a form of Turkic as their main language. The Bulgars long retained many of the customs, military tactics, titles and emblems of a nomadic people of the steppes. |access-date=2020-07-12 |archive-date=2021-12-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211222111911/https://books.google.com/books?id=ZEaSdNBL0sgC |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{sfn|Sophoulis|2011|pp=65–66, 68–69|ps=: "The warriors who founded the Bulgar state in the Lower Danube region were culturally related to the nomads of Eurasia. Indeed, their language was Turkic, and more specifically Oğuric, as is apparent from the isolated words and phrases preserved in a number of inventory inscriptions." ... "It is generally believed that during their migration to the Balkans, the Bulgars brought with them or swept along several other groups of Eurasian nomads whose exact ethnic and linguistic affinities are impossible to determine... Sarmato-Alanian origin... Slav or Slavicized sedentary populations."}}{{sfn|Brook|2006|p=13|ps=: "Thus, the Bulgars were actually a tribal confederation of multiple Hunnic, Turkic, and Iranian groups mixed together."}}<ref name="EB_Arrival">{{cite web |url=http://global.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/84090/Bulgaria/42718/Sport-and-recreation#toc42721 |title=Bulgaria: Arrival of the Bulgars |author-link= |date= |website=Encyclopædia Britannica Online |publisher=[[Encyclopædia_Britannica,_Inc.|Encyclopædia Britannica, Inc.]] |access-date=3 June 2015 |quote=The name Bulgaria comes from the Bulgars, a people who are still a matter of academic dispute with respect to their origin (Turkic or Indo-European) as well as to their influence on the ethnic mixture and the language of present-day Bulgaria. }}{{Dead link|date=June 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref name="EB_Bulgars">{{cite web |url=http://global.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/84067/Bulgar |title=Bulgar |author-link= |date= |website=Encyclopædia Britannica Online|publisher=[[Encyclopædia_Britannica,_Inc.|Encyclopædia Britannica, Inc.]] |access-date=3 June 2015 |quote=Although many scholars, including linguists, had posited that the Bulgars were derived from a Turkic tribe of Central Asia (perhaps with Iranian elements), modern genetic research points to an affiliation with western Eurasian populations.}}</ref>。对中亚突厥语人群和其他与保加尔人有关的民族的现代基因学研究发现了保加尔人和亚欧西部民族的亲属关系<ref name="EB_Bulgars"/><ref name="Cenghiz">{{cite web |last=Cenghiz |first=Ilhan |date=2015 |title=Y-DNA Haplogroups in Turkic People |url=https://yhaplogroups.wordpress.com/ |work=yhaplogroups.wordpress.com |access-date=2020-07-12 |archive-date=2021-04-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210426175518/https://yhaplogroups.wordpress.com/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Suslova">{{cite journal |author=Suslova |date=October 2012 |title=HLA gene and haplotype frequencies in Russians, Bashkirs and Tatars, living in the Chelyabinsk Region (Russian South Urals). |journal=International Journal of Immunogenetics |publisher=Blackwell Publishing Ltd |volume=39 |issue=5 |pmid=22520580 |pages=375–392|display-authors=etal |doi=10.1111/j.1744-313X.2012.01117.x}}</ref>。保加尔人使用[[保加尔语|保加尔语]]，这是[[乌古尔语支|乌古尔]][[突厥语|突厥语]]的一种{{sfn|Waldman, Mason|2006|p=106–107}}，他们保存了欧亚草原的军事头衔、组织和习俗{{sfn|Waldman, Mason|2006|p=108–109}}以及[[萨满教|萨满教]]和[[腾格里|腾格里]]信仰{{sfn|Waldman, Mason|2006|p=109}}。

[[邓吉西克|邓吉西克]]死后，[[匈人|匈人]]似乎被其他族群所吸收，如保加尔人{{sfn|Maenchen-Helfen|1973|p=168}}。然而Kim认为匈人仍处在Ernak的统治下，成为{{tsl|en|Kutrigurs|库特古尔}}和{{tsl|en|Utigurs|乌提格尔}}匈-保加尔人{{sfn|Kim|2013|p=123}}。这一结论仍存在争议。一些学者认为另一个在古代文献里被识别为匈人的族群[[北高加索匈人|北高加索匈人]]是真正的匈人{{sfnm|1a1=Kim|1y=2015|1p=136|2a1=Sinor|2y=2005|2p=4228}}。后匈人时代不同草原民族的统治者曾声称是阿提拉的后裔，以便维持其权力的合法性，且4世纪以后若干草原民族也被西欧和东罗马的史料称为匈人{{sfn|Róna-Tas|1999|p=309}}。

保加尔在历史上第一次被明确提及是在480年，他们与东罗马皇帝[[芝諾_(羅馬帝國)|芝诺]]（474 - 491年在位）结盟共同对抗[[东哥特人|东哥特人]]{{sfn|Golden|1992|p=104}}。7世纪亚美尼亚学者{{tsl|en|Anania_Shirakatsi||阿纳尼亚·希拉卡齐}}的地理作品《[[地理_(書籍)|地理]]》（Աշխարհացոյց<small>(传统亚美尼亚文)</small>；Աշխարհացույց<small>(现代亚美尼亚文)</small>）中提到''Kup'i Bulgar''、''Duč'i Bulkar''、''Olxontor Błkar''和移民来的''Č'dar Bulkar''等保加尔部落生活于高加索[[庫班地區|庫班地區]]以北的草原{{sfn|Golden|1992|p=103}}。此外还有一个较为模糊的描述''Ziezi ex quo Vulgares''出现于作者未知的{{tsl|en|Chronography of 354||编年史354}}一书中，这里的{{tsl|en|Ziezi||Ziezi}}指圣经中[[闪姆|闪]]的后代{{sfn|Golden|1992|p=103}}{{sfn|Bowersock, Brown, Grabar|1999|p=354}}。

7世纪保加尔人在东欧大草原上成为一个半定居社会，在635年左右建立了[[旧大保加利亚|旧大保加利亚]]，随后668年被[[可萨汗国|可萨汗国]]吞并。

约679年，[[阿斯巴鲁赫|阿斯巴鲁赫]]汗征服了{{tsl|en|Scythia_Minor||小斯基泰}},打开了前往[[默西亞_(羅馬行省)|默西亞]]的通道，建立了[[保加利亚第一帝国|保加利亚第一帝国]]，保加尔人是该国的政治和军事精英。他们随后与[[东罗马帝国|东罗马帝国]]以及之前已经在此地区定居的[[斯拉夫人|斯拉夫部落]]发生了人口融合{{sfn|Waldman, Mason|2006|p=108}}{{sfn|Golden|2011|p=145, 158, 196}}，并最终斯拉夫化，形成现代[[保加利亚人|保加利亚人]]的祖先{{sfn|Fiedler|2008|p=151|ps=: "...ethnic symbiosis between Slavic commoners and Bulgar elites of Turkic origin, who ultimately gave their name to the Slavic-speaking Bulgarians."}}。

