===蒙古帝国灭亡后的蒙古人政权===

{{main article|北元|卡爾梅克汗國|准噶尔汗国}}
[[File:Qing_Dzungar_wars.jpg|thumb]]与[[准噶尔汗国|准噶尔汗国]]之间的[[準噶爾之役|準噶爾之役]]]]

蒙古帝国灭亡后的蒙古人政权，例如蒙古高原的[[北元|北元]]和[[新疆|新疆]]的[[准噶尔汗国|准噶尔汗国]]，同样都是游牧帝国。在1368年元朝灭亡之后，[[明朝|明朝]]恢复了汉族的统治，并重修了长城。在随后的几个世纪里，蒙古人退居蒙古后建立[[北元|北元]]，尽可能维持他们独立的游牧生活<ref>Encyclopedia of the Peoples of Asia and Oceania, by Barbara A. West, p. 558</ref>。另一方面，[[卫拉特|卫拉特]]蒙古部落建立的[[准噶尔汗国|准噶尔汗国]]从17世纪早期延续至18世纪中期，1756年亡于[[清朝|清朝]]，是最后一个骑马射箭的游牧帝国。

===近现代突厥汗国===
{{Main|哈萨克汗国|诺盖汗国|克里米亚汗国}}

哈萨克汗国（{{lang-kk|Қазақ Хандығы}}, {{lang|kk-Latn|Qazaq Handyǵy}}, {{lang|kk-Arab|قازاق حاندىعى}}）是15世纪至19世纪存在的[[金帐汗国|金帐汗国]]的继承者，其领土大约对应当今的哈萨克斯坦共和国。汗国在鼎盛时期，疆域从[[庫曼汗國|庫曼]]东部（相当于西哈萨克斯坦）直到[[乌兹别克斯坦|乌兹别克斯坦]]、[[卡拉卡尔帕克斯坦共和国|卡拉卡尔帕克斯坦]]和[[锡尔河|锡尔河]]大部分地区，并与[[阿斯特拉罕|阿斯特拉罕]]（今属俄罗斯）和[[呼罗珊|呼罗珊]]（今属伊朗）展开军事对抗。哈萨克汗国也参与了俄罗斯和中亚的奴隶活动，后来因卫拉特和准噶尔的一系列入侵而衰弱，进一步瓦解为三个[[玉茲|玉茲]]，逐渐失去了主权并被纳入不断扩张的[[俄罗斯帝国|俄罗斯帝国]]中。 哈萨克汗国的成立标志着现代哈萨克斯坦建国的开始<ref name=ehist1>{{cite web |title=Kazakh Khanate – 550th anniversary |url=http://e-history.kz/en/project/view/3?type=publications&material_id=954 |website=e-history.kz |access-date=2020-07-12 |archive-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191029064528/https://e-history.kz/en/project/view/3?type=publications&material_id=954 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，哈萨克斯坦于2015年庆祝了哈萨克汗国成立550周年<ref>{{cite news |title=Kazakhstan to Celebrate 550th Kazakh Statehood Anniversary in 2015 |url=http://astanatimes.com/2014/10/kazakhstan-celebrate-550th-kazakh-statehood-anniversary-2015/ |work=Astana Times |accessdate=2020-07-12 |archive-date=2014-11-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110150658/http://www.astanatimes.com/2014/10/kazakhstan-celebrate-550th-kazakh-statehood-anniversary-2015/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==常见误解==

一些人错误地认为[[满族|满族]]是游牧民族<ref>Pamela Crossley, ''The Manchus'', p. 3</ref>，实际上他们不是游牧的<ref>Patricia Buckley Ebrey et al., [https://books.google.com/books?id=QfkWAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA271&dq=%22the+manchus+were+not+nomads%22&hl=zh-CN&sa=X&ei=NommUtWDMczaoATT6IHgDQ&ved=0CDkQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=%22the%20manchus%20were%20not%20nomads%22&f=false ''East Asia: A Cultural, Social, and Political History''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QfkWAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA271&dq=%22the+manchus+were+not+nomads%22&hl=zh-CN&sa=X&ei=NommUtWDMczaoATT6IHgDQ&ved=0CDkQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=%22the%20manchus%20were%20not%20nomads%22&f=false |date=20210529081435 }}, 3rd edition, p. 271</ref><ref>Frederic Wakeman, Jr., [https://books.google.com/books?id=8nXLwSG2O8AC&pg=PA24&dq=%22the+manchus+were+not+nomads%22&hl=zh-CN&sa=X&ei=NommUtWDMczaoATT6IHgDQ#v=onepage&q=%22the%20manchus%20were%20not%20nomads%22&f=false ''The Great Enterprise: The Manchu Reconstruction of Imperial Order in the Seventeenth Century''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8nXLwSG2O8AC&pg=PA24&dq=%22the+manchus+were+not+nomads%22&hl=zh-CN&sa=X&ei=NommUtWDMczaoATT6IHgDQ#v=onepage&q=%22the%20manchus%20were%20not%20nomads%22&f=false |date=20210528090443 }}, p. 24, note 1</ref>，而是一个住在固定的村庄、种植粮食、进行渔猎的定居民族。

[[肃慎|肃慎]]使用头部为燧石的木箭进行耕种和渔猎，并居住在山洞和树林里<ref>[https://www.jstor.org/stable/2719229?seq=8 Huang 1990] {{Wayback|url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/2719229?seq=8 |date=20210322113104 }} p. 246.</ref>。肃慎或稷真曾出现于[[山海经|山海经]]和[[魏书|魏书]]中，指的是[[通古斯民族|通古斯]][[靺鞨|靺鞨]]部落<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zh.wikisource.org/wiki/%E9%80%B8%E5%91%A8%E6%9B%B8#.E7.8E.8B.E6.9C.83|title=逸周書|accessdate=18 March 2015|archive-date=2021-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211020144531/https://zh.wikisource.org/wiki/%E9%80%B8%E5%91%A8%E6%9B%B8#.E7.8E.8B.E6.9C.83|dead-url=no}}</ref>。靺鞨喜食猪肉，大量养猪，主要是定居的<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=KHwPAAAAYAAJ&q=The+Mohe+tribes+can+be+characterized+as+having+mostly+a+sedentary+way+of+life.+Pig+breeding+was+the+main+branch+of+their+stockraising+(the+same+can+be+said+about+the+Sushen).+The+richest+PROLEGOMENA+TO+MANCHU+STUDIES+13.&dq=The+Mohe+tribes+can+be+characterized+as+having+mostly+a+sedentary+way+of+life.+Pig+breeding+was+the+main+branch+of+their+stockraising+(the+same+can+be+said+about+the+Sushen).+The+richest+PROLEGOMENA+TO+MANCHU+STUDIES+13.&hl=en&sa=X&ei=WxTkU4CtNffesAT474LgCg&ved=0CB0Q6AEwAA Gorelova 2002] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KHwPAAAAYAAJ&q=The+Mohe+tribes+can+be+characterized+as+having+mostly+a+sedentary+way+of+life.+Pig+breeding+was+the+main+branch+of+their+stockraising+(the+same+can+be+said+about+the+Sushen).+The+richest+PROLEGOMENA+TO+MANCHU+STUDIES+13.&dq=The+Mohe+tribes+can+be+characterized+as+having+mostly+a+sedentary+way+of+life.+Pig+breeding+was+the+main+branch+of+their+stockraising+(the+same+can+be+said+about+the+Sushen).+The+richest+PROLEGOMENA+TO+MANCHU+STUDIES+13.&hl=en&sa=X&ei=WxTkU4CtNffesAT474LgCg&ved=0CB0Q6AEwAA |date=20200808221907 }}, pp. 13–4.</ref>，还使用猪皮和狗皮作外套。他们主要是农民，除了打猎以外，还种植大豆、小麦、小米和大米<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=KHwPAAAAYAAJ&q=raising+(the+same+can+be+said+about+the+Sushen).+The+richest+of+them+possessed+large+flocks+of+pigs,+which+mounted+to+hundreds+of+heads.+They+liked+eating+pork,+and+pig-skins+were+used+by+them+for+sewing+winter+coats+(again+like+the+Sushen).+The+Mohes+also+bred+dogs,+from+whose+skins+they+sewed+fur+coats.....The+Mohe+were+mainly+engaged+in+developed+agriculture,+as+they+used+a+plough,+pushing+it+in+front,+and+pairs+of+horses+as+drought+power.+They+sowed+wheat,+millet,+rice+plants,+and+soybean,+and+used+rice+for+preparing+special+liqueur.&dq=raising+(the+same+can+be+said+about+the+Sushen).+The+richest+of+them+possessed+large+flocks+of+pigs,+which+mounted+to+hundreds+of+heads.+They+liked+eating+pork,+and+pig-skins+were+used+by+them+for+sewing+winter+coats+(again+like+the+Sushen).+The+Mohes+also+bred+dogs,+from+whose+skins+they+sewed+fur+coats.....The+Mohe+were+mainly+engaged+in+developed+agriculture,+as+they+used+a+plough,+pushing+it+in+front,+and+pairs+of+horses+as+drought+power.+They+sowed+wheat,+millet,+rice+plants,+and+soybean,+and+used+rice+for+preparing+special+liqueur.&hl=en&sa=X&ei=IxbkU8C5K-jIsASOgYLACA&ved=0CBsQ6AEwAA Gorelova 2002] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KHwPAAAAYAAJ&q=raising+(the+same+can+be+said+about+the+Sushen).+The+richest+of+them+possessed+large+flocks+of+pigs,+which+mounted+to+hundreds+of+heads.+They+liked+eating+pork,+and+pig-skins+were+used+by+them+for+sewing+winter+coats+(again+like+the+Sushen).+The+Mohes+also+bred+dogs,+from+whose+skins+they+sewed+fur+coats.....The+Mohe+were+mainly+engaged+in+developed+agriculture,+as+they+used+a+plough,+pushing+it+in+front,+and+pairs+of+horses+as+drought+power.+They+sowed+wheat,+millet,+rice+plants,+and+soybean,+and+used+rice+for+preparing+special+liqueur.&dq=raising+(the+same+can+be+said+about+the+Sushen).+The+richest+of+them+possessed+large+flocks+of+pigs,+which+mounted+to+hundreds+of+heads.+They+liked+eating+pork,+and+pig-skins+were+used+by+them+for+sewing+winter+coats+(again+like+the+Sushen).+The+Mohes+also+bred+dogs,+from+whose+skins+they+sewed+fur+coats.....The+Mohe+were+mainly+engaged+in+developed+agriculture,+as+they+used+a+plough,+pushing+it+in+front,+and+pairs+of+horses+as+drought+power.+They+sowed+wheat,+millet,+rice+plants,+and+soybean,+and+used+rice+for+preparing+special+liqueur.&hl=en&sa=X&ei=IxbkU8C5K-jIsASOgYLACA&ved=0CBsQ6AEwAA |date=20210322073930 }}, p. 14.</ref>。

[[女真|女真]]是定居民族<ref>[http://pandora.cii.wwu.edu/vajda/ea210/manchu2.html Vajda] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100601205357/http://pandora.cii.wwu.edu/vajda/ea210/manchu2.html |date=2010-06-01 }}</ref>，他们是拥有先进农业技术的农民，以小麦和小米作为谷类作物，种植亚麻，并饲养牛、猪、绵羊和马<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=ST6TRNuWmHsC&pg=PA416&dq=Jurchen++log&hl=en&sa=X&ei=oD7kUseuN87isAT5_YLQCg&ved=0CCgQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Jurchen%20%20log&f=false Sinor 1996] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ST6TRNuWmHsC&pg=PA416&dq=Jurchen++log&hl=en&sa=X&ei=oD7kUseuN87isAT5_YLQCg&ved=0CCgQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Jurchen%20%20log&f=false |date=20210322033052 }}, p. 416.</ref>。他们的耕种生活方式与草原上的蒙古人和契丹人的游牧方式大不相同<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=iN9Tdfdap5MC&pg=PA217&dq=jurchen+sedentary&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Zs0wUoDDGOv94APpnYGIAQ&ved=0CFAQ6wEwBg#v=onepage&q=jurchen%20sedentary&f=false Twitchett, Franke, Fairbank 1994] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iN9Tdfdap5MC&pg=PA217&dq=jurchen+sedentary&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Zs0wUoDDGOv94APpnYGIAQ&ved=0CFAQ6wEwBg#v=onepage&q=jurchen%20sedentary&f=false |date=20210322070449 }}, p. 217.</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=kG45gi7E3hsC&pg=PA112&dq=Jurchen+Chin+farming+background+inclined+to+cultural+assimilation+with+agricultural+society+of+China&hl=en&sa=X&ei=lpdRU6nWKue0sQSso4HwAg&ved=0CCsQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Jurchen%20Chin%20farming%20background%20inclined%20to%20cultural%20assimilation%20with%20agricultural%20society%20of%20China&f=false de Rachewiltz 1993] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kG45gi7E3hsC&pg=PA112&dq=Jurchen+Chin+farming+background+inclined+to+cultural+assimilation+with+agricultural+society+of+China&hl=en&sa=X&ei=lpdRU6nWKue0sQSso4HwAg&ved=0CCsQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Jurchen%20Chin%20farming%20background%20inclined%20to%20cultural%20assimilation%20with%20agricultural%20society%20of%20China&f=false |date=20210416231357 }}, p. 112.</ref>。女真人最多也只能被描述为“半游牧”，而其中大多数是定居的<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=wZx0VvujPqcC&printsec=frontcover&hl=en#v=onepage&q=semi-nomadic&f=false  Breuker 2010] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wZx0VvujPqcC&printsec=frontcover&hl=en#v=onepage&q=semi-nomadic&f=false |date=20200806022929 }}, p. 221.</ref>。

满族的生活方式（经济）被描述为农业、种植谷物并饲养动物<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=glU0vte5gSkC&pg=PA828#v=onepage&q&f=false Wurm 1996] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=glU0vte5gSkC&pg=PA828#v=onepage&q&f=false |date=20211130055104 }}, p. 828.</ref>。满族在[[沈阳|沈阳]]以北从事[[刀耕火种|刀耕火种]]的农业<ref>[https://www.jstor.org/stable/3985584?seq=2 Reardon-Anderson 2000] {{Wayback|url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/3985584?seq=2 |date=20200807074355 }}, p. 504.</ref>。海西女真是“半农业的”，建州女真和毛怜女真则是定居的，而渔猎是野人女真的生活方式<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=tyhT9SZRLS8C&pg=PA266&dq=jurchen+sedentary&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Zs0wUoDDGOv94APpnYGIAQ&ved=0CF0Q6AEwCQ#v=onepage&q=jurchen%20sedentary&f=false Mote, Twitchett & Fairbank 1988] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tyhT9SZRLS8C&pg=PA266&dq=jurchen+sedentary&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Zs0wUoDDGOv94APpnYGIAQ&ved=0CF0Q6AEwCQ#v=onepage&q=jurchen%20sedentary&f=false |date=20210321233822 }}, p. 266.</ref>。汉族社会与定居且从事农耕的建州和毛怜女真比较像<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=tVhvh6ibLJcC&pg=PA258&dq=chien+chou+mao+lien+sedentary&hl=en&sa=X&ei=aI3TU46MOs_nsASPv4HIDg&ved=0CCsQ6wEwAQ#v=onepage&q=chien%20chou%20mao%20lien%20sedentary&f=false Twitchett & Mote 1998] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tVhvh6ibLJcC&pg=PA258&dq=chien+chou+mao+lien+sedentary&hl=en&sa=X&ei=aI3TU46MOs_nsASPv4HIDg&ved=0CCsQ6wEwAQ#v=onepage&q=chien%20chou%20mao%20lien%20sedentary&f=false |date=20210322140056 }}, p. 258.</ref>。狩猎、骑马射箭、畜牧和定居的农业都是建州女真文化的一部分<ref>[https://www.jstor.org/stable/2646525?seq=6 Rawski 1996] {{Wayback|url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/2646525?seq=6 |date=20210418071033 }}, p. 834.</ref>。虽然满族人练习射箭和骑马，但满族的直属祖先从事定居农业<ref>[https://archive.org/details/lastemperorssoc00raws/page/43 Rawski 1998], p. 43.</ref>。虽然满族也进行狩猎，但他们是定居民族<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=WFls6zdc40QC&pg=PA215#v=onepage&q&f=false Allsen 2011] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WFls6zdc40QC&pg=PA215#v=onepage&q&f=false |date=20210415175646 }}, p. 215.</ref>。他们的主要生产方式是农耕，他们居住在城墙包围的村庄、要塞和城镇，他们的金朝女真祖先也从事耕种<ref>{{cite book|title=Transactions, American Philosophical Society (vol. 36, Part 1, 1946)|url=https://books.google.com/?id=g08LAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA10&dq=Marriages+between+Manchu+girls+and+Chinese+deserters+were+officially+promoted+during+the+early+years+of+the+dynasty.#v=onepage&q=Marriages+between+Manchu+girls+and+Chinese+deserters+were+officially+promoted+during+the+early+years+of+the+dynasty.&f=false|publisher=American Philosophical Society|isbn=978-1-4223-7719-2|pages=10–}}</ref><ref name="WittfogelFêng1949">{{cite book|author1=Karl August Wittfogel|author2=Chia-shêng Fêng|title=History of Chinese Society: Liao, 907–1125|url=https://books.google.com/?id=c35CAAAAYAAJ&q=Marriages+between+Manchu+girls+and+Chinese+deserters+were+officially+promoted+during+the+early+years+of+the+dynasty.&dq=Marriages+between+Manchu+girls+and+Chinese+deserters+were+officially+promoted+during+the+early+years+of+the+dynasty.|year=1949|publisher=American Philosophical Society|page=10}}</ref>。

